{
  "texts": [
    "Supporters had vocational training/trade certificates (1 respondent), Bachelor's degree or equivalent (7), or postgraduate degree (5), and 1 preferred not to answer.",
    "People with dementia received the diagnosis between 1 and 13 years (µ = 5.1) ago.",
    "They were diagnosed with various types of dementia, namely Alzheimer's disease (9 respondents), Vascular dementia (1), Fronto-temporal dementia (1), Lewy body dementia (1), or Mixed Dementia (2), and 1 preferred not to answer.",
    "When asked to freely describe their symptoms, memory problems were mentioned most often, with 5 respondents mentioned problems with \"short term memory\", and another one \"total blank in the mornings\".",
    "Additional symptoms were related to social interaction (\"withdrawn from people\", \"unable to speak properly, difficulty understanding conversations\"), physical symptoms (\"tremors, gait and balance\", \"difficult to balance on one side\", \"shakes, unstable\"), as well as \"hallucinations, visual and auditory\" and a general \"inability to perform everyday tasks\" and \"inability to understand controls on oven or television\"."
  ]
}